The paper discusses the use of Apache Mesos for resource management in a multicloud environment, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of NAT firewall for making nodes/VMs visible to Mesos, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the design of a meta-scheduler, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of Apache Airavata for job scheduling, which falls under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of multiple clouds and clusters, which falls under the category of distributed systems (cs.Distributed Systems).
